		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Re: Several Famicom Nes Documents... in Japanese</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />One nifty thing: it tells us how the VRC2 Microwire EEPROM was <em>supposed</em> to have worked: Writes to $6000-$6FFF were latched, and the 3 least significant bits of the byte written were: &amp;1- DataToEeprom &amp;2-SK &amp;4- CS. Reads of $6000-$6FFF should have returned the value DataFromEeprom as the least significant bit.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


