	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />The VRC6 documentation seems to only describe what we currently know as the &quot;mirroring control register&quot; at $B003 - apparently, it does quite a lot more than that. From what I can tell, the VRC6 has the ability to map either CHR ROM or CHR RAM (not sure if the chip has separate enables for the two) into the nametables, much like the Namco 163 mapper.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


