		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Other interesting things:<br />* In the version of the 2A03 described here, pin 30 was instead part of a on-chip crystal driver for the CPU<br />* We now have official (awful) names for all the registers<br />* They initially were going to release the MMC3 in a 42-pin DIP or SOP (Probably the same as the MMC2?)

		

		</td>
