	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />The official APU registers names are WRA0, WRA1, WRA2, WRA3, WRB0, WRB1 … WRE3, WRF0, RDST/WRST, RDP0/WRP0, RDP1/SoftCLK<br />I think that's worse than using the numbers.<br />The official PPU register names are CTLR0, CTLR1, SR, OAM.AR, OAM, SCC, VRAM.AR, and VRAM<br />I don't know how many assemblers support periods in the middle of symbols.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
